{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbc4766b8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3020d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3020d"},"text":"§ 3020d.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Surplus property eligibility","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any State or local government agency, and any nonprofit organization or institution, which receives funds appropriated for programs for older individuals under this chapter, under title IV or title XX of the Social Security Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s601"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 601","children":[],"tail":" et seq., 1397 et seq.], or under titles VIII and X of the Economic Opportunity Act of 1964 ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s2991"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 2991","children":[],"tail":" et seq., 2996 et seq.] and the Community Services Block Grant Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s9901"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 9901","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], shall be deemed eligible to receive for such programs, property which is declared surplus to the needs of the Federal Government in accordance with laws applicable to surplus property."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbc4766b9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/73/tII/s213"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–73, title II, § 213","children":[],"tail":", formerly § 214, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/478/tI/s102/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–478, title I, § 102(i)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-18"},"text":"Oct. 18, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/1516"},"text":"92 Stat. 1516","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 213 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/115/s2/e/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–115, § 2(e)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (k), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/1596"},"text":"95 Stat. 1596","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbc4766ba-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbc4766bb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbc4766bc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Social Security Act, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"act Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/620"},"text":"49 Stat. 620","children":[],"tail":", as Titles IV and XX of the Social Security Act are classified generally to subchapters IV (§ 601 et seq.) and XX (§ 1397 et seq.), respectively, of chapter 7 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1305"},"text":"section 1305 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Economic Opportunity Act of 1964, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/452"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–452","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-08-20"},"text":"Aug. 20, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/508"},"text":"78 Stat. 508","children":[],"tail":", which was classified generally to chapter 34 (§ 2701 et 